com.sinch.android.rtc

Interface NotificationResult


  • public interface NotificationResult
    The NotificationResult is used to indicate the result of a relayed push notification (SinchClient.relayRemotePushNotificationPayload(java.lang.String)).

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      CallNotificationResult getCallResult()
      If the push notification is call related (isCall() is true), this method returns a CallNotificationResult.
      String getDisplayName()
      The display name of the user calling or sending the message, if available.
      MessageNotificationResult getMessageResult()
      If the push notification is message related (isMessage() is true), this method returns a MessageNotificationResult.
      boolean isCall()
      Indicates whether the push notification is call related.
      boolean isMessage()
      Indicates whether the push notification is message related.
      boolean isValid()
      Indicates whether the push notification is valid.

    • Method Detail

      • isValid

        boolean isValid()
        Indicates whether the push notification is valid.
        Returns:
        true if the push notification is valid, otherwise false.

      • isCall

        boolean isCall()
        Indicates whether the push notification is call related.

      • isMessage

        Indicates whether the push notification is message related.

      • getDisplayName

        String getDisplayName()
        The display name of the user calling or sending the message, if available. Only available when the complete Intent was forwarded to SinchClient.relayRemotePushNotificationPayload(Intent) and if the display name was set on the sender side.
        Returns:
        String if available, otherwise null

      • getCallResult

      • getMessageResult
